title: Vote of No Confidence
subtitle: The coalition is fracturing...
new-page: true
view-if: spd_in_government = 1 and coalition_dissent >= 3 and spd_r < 50 and not constructive_vonc
tags: event
on-arrival: {!
// Determine who is calling the vote and why
Q.vonc_caller = "";
Q.vonc_reason = "";
Q.vonc_severity = 0;

// Calculate severity based on dissent level
Q.vonc_severity = Q.coalition_dissent;

// Determine primary antagonist in coalition
if (Q.in_grand_coalition && Q.dvp_relation < 45) {
    Q.vonc_caller = "DVP";
    if (Q.welfare > 0) Q.vonc_reason = "welfare_spending";
    else if (Q.economic_minister_party === "SPD") Q.vonc_reason = "economic_policy";
    else Q.vonc_reason = "general_policy";
} else if (Q.in_grand_coalition && Q.z_relation < 45) {
    Q.vonc_caller = "Z";
    if (Q.judicial_reform > 0) Q.vonc_reason = "judicial_reform";
    else if (Q.secularization > 0) Q.vonc_reason = "church_policy";
    else Q.vonc_reason = "general_policy";
} else if (Q.in_weimar_coalition && Q.z_relation < 45) {
    Q.vonc_caller = "Z";
    if (Q.secularization > 0) Q.vonc_reason = "church_policy";
    else if (Q.foreign_policy_seen && Q.foreign_minister_party === "SPD") Q.vonc_reason = "foreign_policy";
    else Q.vonc_reason = "general_policy";
} else if (Q.in_weimar_coalition && Q.ddp_relation < 45) {
    Q.vonc_caller = Q.ddp_name;
    Q.vonc_reason = "general_policy";
} else if (Q.in_popular_front && Q.z_relation < 40) {
    Q.vonc_caller = "Z";
    Q.vonc_reason = "kpd_cooperation";
} else if (Q.in_popular_front && Q.kpd_relation < 40) {
    Q.vonc_caller = "KPD";
    Q.vonc_reason = "insufficient_socialism";
} else if (Q.in_left_front && Q.kpd_coalition_dissent >= 4) {
    Q.vonc_caller = "KPD";
    Q.vonc_reason = "reformist_betrayal";
} else {
    // Default to largest non-SPD party
    if (Q.in_grand_coalition) Q.vonc_caller = "DVP";
    else if (Q.in_weimar_coalition) Q.vonc_caller = "Z";
    else Q.coalition_dissent = 2;
}

// Calculate votes needed and available
Q.government_votes = Q.coalition_votes;
Q.opposition_votes = 100 - Q.coalition_votes;

// Can KPD save us?
Q.kpd_can_save = (Q.kpd_r >= 10 && Q.kpd_relation >= 50 && Q.communist_coalition >= 3 && !Q.in_popular_front && !Q.in_left_front);
Q.kpd_needed_to_survive = (Q.government_votes + Q.kpd_r >= 50);

// Can DNVP save us (if moderate)?
Q.dnvp_can_save = (Q.dnvp_line !== 3 && Q.dnvp_relation >= 55 && Q.dnvp_r >= 8);

// Calculate concession costs
Q.prussia_concession_available = Q.spd_prussia === 1;
Q.welfare_concession_available = Q.welfare >= 0;
Q.policy_concession_available = Q.vonc_reason !== "general_policy";
!}
go-to: vonc_intro

@vonc_intro

= Vote of No Confidence - [+ coalition_name +]

**Crisis in the coalition!**

The [+ vonc_caller +] has called for a vote of no confidence against the [+ chancellor +] government.

**Their grievance:** [? if vonc_reason = "welfare_spending" : Our welfare spending is bankrupting the state and destroying business confidence. ?][? if vonc_reason = "economic_policy" : Our socialist economic policies are driving away investment and prolonging the depression. ?][? if vonc_reason = "judicial_reform" : Our attacks on the judiciary undermine the rule of law. ?][? if vonc_reason = "church_policy" : Our secularization policies attack the foundations of Christian society. ?][? if vonc_reason = "foreign_policy" : Our foreign policy is too conciliatory toward our former enemies. ?][? if vonc_reason = "kpd_cooperation" : Governing with communists legitimizes revolutionary extremism. ?][? if vonc_reason = "insufficient_socialism" : The SPD has betrayed the working class with half-measures and compromise. ?][? if vonc_reason = "reformist_betrayal" : The SPD's reformism blocks genuine revolutionary change. ?][? if vonc_reason = "general_policy" : The accumulated grievances against this government have become intolerable. ?]

**Current situation:**
- Coalition support: [+ government_votes +]%
- Opposition: [+ opposition_votes +]%
- Coalition dissent level: [+ coalition_dissent +]

[? if vonc_severity >= 5 : The vote is almost certain to succeed unless we make major concessions. ?]
[? if vonc_severity = 4 : The vote will likely succeed unless we can reduce tensions. ?]
[? if vonc_severity = 3 : The vote could go either way. ?]

**What should we do?**

- @vonc_assess_options: Assess our options carefully
- @vonc_let_it_happen: Accept the vote and prepare for new elections

@vonc_assess_options

= Strategic Options

We have several potential paths to survive this crisis:

**1. CONCESSIONS TO COALITION PARTNERS**
[? if prussia_concession_available : - Cede control of Prussia (guarantees survival) ?]
[? if welfare_concession_available : - Major austerity program (likely to work) ?]
[? if policy_concession_available : - Reverse the specific policy they oppose (might work) ?]
- Spend resources on coalition management (uncertain)

**2. SEEK EXTERNAL SUPPORT**
[? if kpd_can_save and kpd_needed_to_survive : - KPD abstention/support (would require bringing them into government) ?]
[? if kpd_can_save and not kpd_needed_to_survive : - KPD abstention (not enough votes to save us) ?]
[? if dnvp_can_save : - DNVP abstention (would require major rightward shift) ?]

**3. PARLIAMENTARY MANEUVERS**
[? if reformist_strength >= 60 : - Purge left-wing of party to reassure partners (risky) ?]
[? if resources >= 5 : - Buy time with emergency resources (temporary) ?]

**4. ACCEPT DEFEAT**
- Resign and call new elections
- Try to form a minority government

**What approach should we take?**

- @vonc_concessions_menu: Make concessions to coalition partners
- @vonc_external_support: Seek external support
- @vonc_maneuvers: Try parliamentary maneuvers
- @vonc_let_it_happen: Accept defeat

# ============================================
# CONCESSIONS TO COALITION PARTNERS
# ============================================

@vonc_concessions_menu

= Concessions

What are we willing to give up to save the government?

- @vonc_prussia: Cede control of Prussia
- @vonc_austerity: Enact emergency austerity
- @vonc_reverse_policy: Reverse the specific policy causing crisis
- @vonc_ministry_reshuffle: Offer ministry reshuffling
- @vonc_resources: Use party resources for coalition management
- @vonc_assess_options: Back to main options

@vonc_prussia
view-if: prussia_concession_available
on-arrival: {!
Q.spd_prussia = 0;
Q.prussian_government = "Coalition";
Q.coalition_dissent = 0;
Q.vonc_resolved = 1;

// Political costs
Q.reformist_dissent += 15;
Q.centrist_dissent += 12;
Q.labor_dissent += 15;
Q.left_dissent += 8;
Q.workers_spd -= 8;
Q.new_middle_spd -= 5;
Q.old_middle_spd -= 6;
Q.unemployed_spd -= 5;

// Benefits to partners
if (Q.in_grand_coalition) {
    Q.dvp_relation += 10;
    Q.z_relation += 8;
}
if (Q.in_weimar_coalition) {
    Q.z_relation += 10;
    Q.ddp_relation += 5;
}
!}

= Prussia Concession

**We have ceded control of the Prussian government.**

The [+ vonc_caller +] has agreed to withdraw the vote of no confidence. Prussia will now be governed by a coalition led by the Center Party.

**Consequences:**
- We no longer control Germany's largest state
- Our organizational base is severely weakened
- The party is outraged at this capitulation
- Coalition partners are satisfied for now

**Internal party reaction:**

*"This is a betrayal of everything we've built in Prussia!"* - Reformist wing

*"We've surrendered our strongest defensive position."* - Centrist faction

*"Typical social democratic cowardice!"* - Left wing

The government survives, but at enormous cost.

- @vonc_aftermath: Continue

@vonc_austerity
view-if: welfare_concession_available
on-arrival: {!
Q.coalition_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.coalition_dissent - 2);
Q.welfare -= 2;
Q.budget += 1;
Q.unemployed += 4;

// Political costs
Q.workers_spd -= 12;
Q.unemployed_spd -= 15;
Q.workers_kpd += 8;
Q.workers_nsdap += 4;
Q.unemployed_kpd += 7;
Q.unemployed_nsdap += 6;
Q.left_dissent += 18;
Q.centrist_dissent += 12;
Q.labor_dissent += 20;

// Coalition benefits
if (Q.in_grand_coalition) {
    Q.dvp_relation += 8;
    Q.z_relation += 3;
}
if (Q.in_weimar_coalition) {
    Q.z_relation += 5;
    Q.ddp_relation += 6;
}

// KPD reaction if in popular front
if (Q.in_popular_front) {
    Q.kpd_coalition_dissent += 2;
    Q.kpd_relation -= 12;
}
if (Q.in_left_front) {
    Q.kpd_coalition_dissent += 3;
    Q.kpd_relation -= 15;
}

Q.vonc_resolved = Q.coalition_dissent < 2;
!}

= Emergency Austerity

**We have enacted a drastic austerity program.**

Welfare benefits are slashed. Unemployment insurance is cut. Public works programs are cancelled.

[? if vonc_resolved : The [+ vonc_caller +] has withdrawn the vote of no confidence. ?]
[? if not vonc_resolved : The [+ vonc_caller +] is somewhat mollified, but still may proceed with the vote. ?]

**Consequences:**
- Unemployment will rise significantly
- Workers and unemployed are abandoning us
- The KPD and NSDAP gain support
- Our left wing is in open revolt
[? if in_popular_front or in_left_front : - The KPD questions our socialist credentials ?]

*"You've betrayed the working class to save your coalition!"* - Left SPD

*"This is exactly what Brüning would do!"* - Trade unions

[? if vonc_resolved : The government survives, but our base is shattered. ?]
[? if not vonc_resolved : We may need additional measures to survive. ?]

- @vonc_aftermath: Continue

@vonc_reverse_policy
view-if: policy_concession_available
on-arrival: {!
Q.coalition_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.coalition_dissent - 2);

if (Q.vonc_reason === "welfare_spending") {
    Q.welfare -= 1;
    Q.workers_spd -= 6;
    Q.unemployed_spd -= 8;
    Q.left_dissent += 10;
    Q.labor_dissent += 12;
    Q.dvp_relation += 6;
}
else if (Q.vonc_reason === "church_policy") {
    Q.secularization -= 1;
    Q.z_relation += 8;
    Q.catholics_spd -= 5;
    Q.left_dissent += 8;
    Q.pro_republic -= 2;
}
else if (Q.vonc_reason === "judicial_reform") {
    Q.judicial_reform -= 1;
    Q.z_relation += 6;
    Q.dvp_relation += 5;
    Q.pro_republic -= 3;
    Q.reformist_dissent += 8;
}
else if (Q.vonc_reason === "economic_policy") {
    Q.nationalization -= 1;
    Q.workers_spd -= 8;
    Q.left_dissent += 12;
    Q.labor_dissent += 10;
    Q.dvp_relation += 8;
}
else if (Q.vonc_reason === "foreign_policy") {
    Q.reparations_negotiation = 0;
    Q.z_relation += 5;
    Q.dvp_relation += 5;
    Q.reformist_dissent += 5;
}

Q.vonc_resolved = Q.coalition_dissent < 2;
!}

= Policy Reversal

**We have reversed the policy that caused this crisis.**

[? if vonc_reason = "welfare_spending" : Welfare spending has been reduced. ?]
[? if vonc_reason = "church_policy" : Our secularization measures have been scaled back. ?]
[? if vonc_reason = "judicial_reform" : Judicial reforms have been suspended. ?]
[? if vonc_reason = "economic_policy" : Socialist economic policies have been moderated. ?]
[? if vonc_reason = "foreign_policy" : We've adopted a harder line in foreign policy. ?]

[? if vonc_resolved : The [+ vonc_caller +] has withdrawn the vote of no confidence. ?]
[? if not vonc_resolved : The [+ vonc_caller +] appreciates this gesture but may still proceed. ?]

The party's left wing is furious at this capitulation to bourgeois pressure.

[? if vonc_resolved : The government survives at the cost of our principles. ?]
[? if not vonc_resolved : We may need additional measures. ?]

- @vonc_aftermath: Continue

@vonc_ministry_reshuffle
choose-if: resources >= 2
unavailable-subtitle: We don't have enough resources (need 2)
on-arrival: {!
Q.resources -= 2;
Q.coalition_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.coalition_dissent - 1);

// Offer ministry to dissenting partner
if (Q.vonc_caller === "DVP") {
    if (Q.economic_minister_party === "SPD") {
        Q.economic_minister_party = "DVP";
        Q.economic_minister = "Curtius";
        Q.dvp_relation += 8;
    } else if (Q.finance_minister_party === "SPD") {
        Q.finance_minister_party = "DVP";
        Q.finance_minister = "Moldenhauer";
        Q.dvp_relation += 8;
    }
    Q.reformist_dissent += 8;
} else if (Q.vonc_caller === "Z") {
    if (Q.interior_minister_party === "SPD") {
        Q.interior_minister_party = "Z";
        Q.interior_minister = "Wirth";
        Q.z_relation += 8;
    } else if (Q.labor_minister_party === "SPD") {
        Q.labor_minister_party = "Z";
        Q.labor_minister = "Stegerwald";
        Q.z_relation += 8;
    }
    Q.labor_dissent += 10;
    Q.left_dissent += 8;
}

Q.vonc_resolved = Q.coalition_dissent < 2;
!}

= Ministry Reshuffle

**We have offered key ministries to our coalition partners.**

[? if vonc_caller = "DVP" : The DVP now controls [? if economic_minister_party = "DVP" : Economic Affairs ?][? if finance_minister_party = "DVP" : Finance ?]. ?]
[? if vonc_caller = "Z" : The Center Party now controls [? if interior_minister_party = "Z" : Interior ?][? if labor_minister_party = "Z" : Labor ?]. ?]

[? if vonc_resolved : The [+ vonc_caller +] has withdrawn the vote of no confidence. ?]
[? if not vonc_resolved : The [+ vonc_caller +] appreciates this but may still proceed. ?]

Our party is unhappy about surrendering influence in government.

- @vonc_aftermath: Continue

@vonc_resources
choose-if: resources >= 3
unavailable-subtitle: We don't have enough resources (need 3)
on-arrival: {!
Q.resources -= 3;
Q.coalition_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.coalition_dissent - 1);
Q.vonc_resolved = Q.coalition_dissent < 2;

if (Q.vonc_caller === "DVP") Q.dvp_relation += 3;
if (Q.vonc_caller === "Z") Q.z_relation += 3;
if (Q.vonc_caller === Q.ddp_name) Q.ddp_relation += 3;
!}

= Coalition Management

**We've used party resources to smooth over tensions.**

Backroom deals, patronage, and careful negotiation have reduced immediate tensions.

[? if vonc_resolved : The [+ vonc_caller +] has withdrawn the vote of no confidence. ?]
[? if not vonc_resolved : This buys us some time, but fundamental issues remain. ?]

This is only a temporary solution - the underlying conflicts persist.

- @vonc_aftermath: Continue

# ============================================
# EXTERNAL SUPPORT OPTIONS
# ============================================

@vonc_external_support

= External Support

We can try to survive the vote by seeking support from parties outside our coalition.

**Options:**

[? if kpd_can_save : - **KPD Abstention/Support**: The Communists could save us, but would demand entrance to government ?]

[? if dnvp_can_save : - **DNVP Abstention**: The moderate nationalists might abstain, but would demand major concessions ?]

[? if not kpd_can_save and not dnvp_can_save : No external parties are both willing and able to help us. ?]

- @vonc_kpd_support: Approach the KPD
- @vonc_dnvp_support: Approach the DNVP
- @vonc_assess_options: Back to main options

@vonc_kpd_support
view-if: kpd_can_save
on-arrival: {!
Q.kpd_demands_seen = 1;
!}

= KPD Support

We've approached the KPD leadership about saving the government.

[? if kpd_party_leader = "Conciliators" : The Conciliator leadership is open to discussion. ?]
[? if kpd_party_leader != "Conciliators" : Even the hardline KPD leadership sees an opportunity here. ?]

**KPD Position:**

"We won't simply abstain to save a bourgeois coalition. If you want our votes, we enter the government as full partners with real power over policy."

**Their demands:**
- Entry into the coalition with significant ministries
- Immediate pro-worker legislation
- Crackdown on fascist organizations
- Progressive taxation of capital

[? if in_grand_coalition : This would transform the Grand Coalition into a Popular Front. The DVP would certainly leave. ?]
[? if in_weimar_coalition : This would create a Left Coalition. The Center Party might leave. ?]

**What should we do?**

- @vonc_kpd_accept: Accept KPD entry into government
- @vonc_kpd_reject: Reject their terms
- @vonc_assess_options: Consider other options

@vonc_kpd_accept
on-arrival: {!
Q.communist_coalition += 1;
Q.workers_kpd += 3;
Q.kpd_relation += 10;
Q.coalition_dissent = 0;
Q.vonc_resolved = 1;

// Transform coalition
if (Q.in_grand_coalition) {
    Q.in_grand_coalition = 0;
    Q.in_popular_front = 1;
    Q.coalition_name = "Popular Front";
    Q.dvp_in_government = 0;
    Q.kpd_in_government = 1;
    
    // Reassign DVP ministries
    if (Q.economic_minister_party === "DVP") {
        Q.economic_minister_party = "KPD";
        Q.economic_minister = "Remmele";
    }
    if (Q.finance_minister_party === "DVP") {
        Q.finance_minister_party = "SPD";
        Q.finance_minister = "Hilferding";
    }
    
    Q.coup_progress += 3;
    Q.capital_strike_progress += 2;
}
else if (Q.in_weimar_coalition) {
    Q.in_weimar_coalition = 0;
    Q.coalition_name = "Left Coalition";
    Q.kpd_in_government = 1;
    
    if (Q.interior_minister_party === "Z") {
        Q.interior_minister_party = "KPD";
        Q.interior_minister = "Ulbricht";
    }
    
    Q.coup_progress += 2;
}

Q.left_dissent -= 10;
Q.labor_dissent -= 8;
Q.reformist_dissent += 15;
Q.centrist_dissent += 12;
!}

= KPD Enters Government

**Historic breakthrough! The KPD has entered the government!**

[? if in_popular_front : The Grand Coalition has been transformed into a Popular Front. The DVP has left in protest. ?]
[? if coalition_name = "Left Coalition" : A Left Coalition now governs Germany. ?]

**New Coalition Composition:**
- SPD
- KPD
[? if in_popular_front : - Center Party ?]
[? if in_popular_front : - [+ ddp_name +] ?]
[? if z_in_government and not in_popular_front : - Center Party ?]

**Reactions:**

*"The Bolsheviks are in power! Germany faces revolution!"* - Right-wing press

*"Finally, workers' unity has been achieved!"* - KPD

*"This is a dangerous gamble."* - Reformist SPD

*"At last, real socialist policies!"* - Left SPD

[? if in_popular_front : The Center Party's progressive wing barely convinced the party to stay in government. ?]

The vote of no confidence has been withdrawn. The right-wing is preparing for confrontation.

- @vonc_aftermath: Continue

@vonc_kpd_reject
on-arrival: kpd_relation -= 5

We've decided not to bring the KPD into government at this time.

- @vonc_external_support: Consider other options

@vonc_dnvp_support
view-if: dnvp_can_save
on-arrival: {!
Q.dnvp_demands_seen = 1;
!}

= DNVP Support

We've approached the moderate wing of the DNVP about abstaining on the vote.

**DNVP Position:**

"We could abstain, but we need to see a fundamental shift in your policies. No more socialism, no more weakness on national questions."

**Their demands:**
- End welfare expansion
- Stronger national defense
- Opposition to Young Plan
- Cabinet reshuffle to exclude left-wingers

This would essentially end social democratic governance in favor of a conservative coalition with SPD participation.

**What should we do?**

- @vonc_dnvp_accept: Accept their terms
- @vonc_dnvp_reject: Reject this betrayal
- @vonc_assess_options: Consider other options

@vonc_dnvp_accept
on-arrival: {!
Q.welfare -= 1;
Q.dnvp_relation += 10;
Q.coalition_dissent = 0;
Q.vonc_resolved = 1;

Q.workers_spd -= 10;
Q.left_dissent += 20;
Q.labor_dissent += 18;
Q.centrist_dissent += 10;
Q.reformist_dissent += 8;

Q.workers_kpd += 8;
Q.workers_nsdap += 3;

if (Q.labor_minister_party === "SPD") {
    Q.labor_minister_party = "Z";
    Q.labor_minister = "Stegerwald";
}
!}

= DNVP Deal

**We've struck a deal with the DNVP.**

The vote of no confidence has been withdrawn, but at enormous cost to our principles.

**Consequences:**
- Welfare cuts enacted
- Pro-worker policies abandoned
- Conservative influence increased
- Party left wing in revolt

*"This is the final proof that social democracy serves capitalism!"* - KPD

*"You've sold out the workers for power!"* - Left SPD

*"Sometimes survival requires compromise."* - Reformist leadership

The government survives, but our socialist credibility is shattered.

- @vonc_aftermath: Continue

@vonc_dnvp_reject
on-arrival: dnvp_relation -= 3

We will not betray our principles for DNVP support.

- @vonc_external_support: Consider other options

# ============================================
# PARLIAMENTARY MANEUVERS
# ============================================

@vonc_maneuvers

= Parliamentary Maneuvers

What political tactics should we employ?

- @vonc_purge_left: Purge the left wing to reassure partners
- @vonc_emergency_resources: Emergency resource mobilization
- @vonc_assess_options: Back to main options

@vonc_purge_left
view-if: reformist_strength >= 60
choose-if: left_strength >= 20
unavailable-subtitle: [? if left_strength < 20 : The left wing isn't strong enough to purge. ?]
on-arrival: {!
Q.left_strength -= 15;
Q.reformist_strength += 5;
Q.left_dissent += 25;
Q.labor_dissent += 15;
Q.workers_spd -= 8;

if (Q.in_grand_coalition) {
    Q.dvp_relation += 8;
    Q.z_relation += 5;
}
if (Q.in_weimar_coalition) {
    Q.z_relation += 6;
}

Q.coalition_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.coalition_dissent - 2);
Q.vonc_resolved = Q.coalition_dissent < 2;
!}

= Left Wing Purged

**The party leadership has expelled prominent left-wingers.**

Several left-wing Reichstag deputies have been removed from the parliamentary faction. Others have been demoted or marginalized.

[? if vonc_resolved : Coalition partners are satisfied. The vote has been withdrawn. ?]
[? if not vonc_resolved : Coalition partners appreciate this but want more. ?]

**Consequences:**
- Left wing decimated
- Party discipline improved
- Worker support declining
- Bourgeois partners reassured

*"The reformists have shown their true colors!"* - Left SPD

*"Necessary to maintain coalition viability."* - Party leadership

[? if vonc_resolved : The government survives, but the party is fractured. ?]

- @vonc_aftermath: Continue

@vonc_emergency_resources
choose-if: resources >= 5
unavailable-subtitle: We need 5 resources for this
on-arrival: {!
Q.resources -= 5;
Q.coalition_dissent = Math.max(0, Q.coalition_dissent - 2);
Q.vonc_resolved = Q.coalition_dissent < 2;

if (Q.vonc_caller === "DVP") Q.dvp_relation += 5;
if (Q.vonc_caller === "Z") Q.z_relation += 5;
!}

= Emergency Measures

**We've mobilized all available party resources.**

Through intense lobbying, patronage, and political dealmaking, we've temporarily stabilized the coalition.

[? if vonc_resolved : The vote has been withdrawn. ?]
[? if not vonc_resolved : We've bought time, but fundamental problems remain. ?]

This is extremely expensive and only delays the inevitable unless we address root causes.

- @vonc_aftermath: Continue

# ============================================
# LET IT HAPPEN - GOVERNMENT FALLS
# ============================================

@vonc_let_it_happen
on-arrival: {!
Q.spd_in_government = 0;
Q.in_grand_coalition = 0;
Q.in_weimar_coalition = 0;
Q.in_popular_front = 0;
Q.in_left_front = 0;
Q.spd_toleration = 0;
Q.coalition_dissent = 0;
Q.time_to_election = 3;
Q.pro_republic -= 5;

Q.old_middle_spd -= 3;
Q.new_middle_spd -= 2;
Q.workers_spd -= 3;

if (Q.pro_republic < 50) {
    Q.workers_spd -= 4;
    Q.old_middle_nsdap += 4;
    Q.new_middle_nsdap += 3;
}

// Set up new government
if (Q.president === "Hindenburg") {
    Q.chancellor = "Brüning";
    Q.chancellor_party = "Z";
    Q.welfare -= 2;
    Q.presidential_government = 1;
} else {
    Q.spd_caretaker = 1;
}

// Reset ministries to bourgeois coalition
Q.foreign_minister_party = "DVP";
Q.interior_minister_party = "Z";
Q.justice_minister_party = "I";
Q.labor_minister_party = "Z";
Q.reichswehr_minister_party = "I";
Q.economic_minister_party = Q.ddp_name;
Q.finance_minister_party = "DVP";
Q.agriculture_minister_party = "Z";

Q.labor_minister = "Stegerwald";
Q.interior_minister = "Wirth";
Q.finance_minister = "Moldenhauer";
Q.economic_minister = "Curtius";
Q.justice_minister = "Koch-Weser";
Q.foreign_minister = "Stresemann";
Q.agriculture_minister = "Dietrich";
Q.reichswehr_minister = "Groener";
!}
call: set_next_election_time
go-to: vonc_fall_hindenburg if president = "Hindenburg"; vonc_fall_braun if president = "Braun"

@vonc_fall_hindenburg
on-arrival: {!
// Hindenburg appoints bourgeois government
Q.government_type = "presidential";
Q.minority_government = 1;

// Calculate new government composition
var bourgeois_total = Q.z_r + Q.dvp_r + Q.ddp_r + Q.bvp_r;
Q.minority_government_support = bourgeois_total;

// Check if SPD will tolerate
Q.toleration_offered = (Q.pro_republic >= 40 && Q.nazi_urgency >= 5 && Q.dnvp_line === 3);
!}

= Government Falls - Presidential Appointment

**The vote of no confidence has succeeded.**

The [+ chancellor +] government has resigned. President Hindenburg has appointed **Heinrich Brüning** (Center Party) as Chancellor of a minority bourgeois government.

**New Government Composition:**
- Center Party (Z)
- German People's Party (DVP)
- [+ ddp_name +]
- Bavarian People's Party (BVP)

**Combined Support:** [+ minority_government_support +]%

Brüning immediately announces emergency austerity measures using Article 48 presidential decree powers, bypassing the Reichstag.

**His first acts:**
- Welfare spending slashed
- Unemployment benefits cut
- Public sector wages reduced
- Emergency taxes on workers

[? if toleration_offered : **A difficult choice approaches:** Should the SPD tolerate this government to prevent something worse, or oppose it and force new elections? ?]

[? if not toleration_offered : New elections have been scheduled for [+ next_election_month : month +] [+ next_election_year +]. ?]

- @vonc_toleration_decision: Continue

@vonc_toleration_decision
view-if: toleration_offered

= The Toleration Question

**Brüning's government lacks a Reichstag majority.**

As the largest party, we can bring down this government at any time with a vote of no confidence. However, new elections might benefit the extremists.

**Arguments for Toleration:**

*"The Nazis and Communists would gain in new elections. We must be the responsible party and prevent chaos."* - Otto Wels

*"Brüning's austerity is harmful, but a Nazi-DNVP government would be catastrophic."* - Reformist wing

*"Sometimes we must tolerate lesser evils to prevent greater ones."* - Rudolf Hilferding

**Arguments Against:**

*"Tolerating these attacks on workers makes us complicit! We're betraying our base!"* - Left wing

*"Brüning's policies will only create more unemployment and radicalization."* - Trade unions

*"We become the fig leaf for bourgeois dictatorship!"* - Left SPD deputies

**What should we do?**

- @vonc_accept_toleration: Tolerate the Brüning government
- @vonc_reject_toleration: Oppose and force new elections
- @vonc_conditional_toleration: Tolerate with conditions

@vonc_accept_toleration
on-arrival: {!
Q.spd_toleration = 1;
Q.in_minority_government = 0;
Q.time_to_election = 0; // Cancel immediate elections

// Political consequences
Q.workers_spd -= 8;
Q.unemployed_spd -= 10;
Q.workers_kpd += 6;
Q.unemployed_kpd += 7;
Q.workers_nsdap += 2;
Q.unemployed_nsdap += 3;

Q.left_dissent += 15;
Q.labor_dissent += 18;
Q.centrist_dissent += 8;
Q.reformist_dissent += 5;

// Relationship effects
Q.z_relation += 5;
Q.kpd_relation -= 10;
Q.dnvp_relation += 3;

// Next election in 2 years instead
Q.next_election_year = Q.year + 2;
Q.next_election_month = Q.month;
Q.next_election_time = Q.time + 24;

Q.toleration_policy_points = 0; // Track concessions we extract
!}

= Toleration Policy Adopted

**The SPD will tolerate the Brüning government.**

We will not vote no confidence, allowing Brüning to govern via presidential decree. However, we reserve the right to oppose specific policies and demand concessions.

**Immediate Reactions:**

*"The SPD has betrayed the working class!"* - KPD

*"Responsible statesmanship in difficult times."* - Center Party

*"Social Democrats prop up capitalist dictatorship!"* - Communist press

*"Cowardly surrender!"* - Left wing SPD

**Within the party:**
- Left wing threatens split
- Trade unions are furious
- Reformists defend the decision
- Workers are abandoning us for KPD

**The situation:**
- No immediate elections
- We can influence policy from opposition
- Brüning's austerity will continue
- The party is deeply divided

This "toleration" arrangement is unprecedented and unstable. How long can we maintain it?

- @vonc_aftermath: Continue

@vonc_reject_toleration
on-arrival: {!
Q.spd_toleration = 0;
Q.time_to_election = 3;

// Set elections
Q.next_election_year = Q.year;
Q.next_election_month = Q.month + 3;
if (Q.next_election_month > 12) {
    Q.next_election_month -= 12;
    Q.next_election_year += 1;
}
Q.next_election_time = Q.time + 3;

// Party unity benefits
Q.left_dissent -= 5;
Q.labor_dissent -= 5;
Q.workers_spd += 2;

// But instability costs
Q.pro_republic -= 3;
Q.coup_progress += 1;

Q.z_relation -= 5;
Q.kpd_relation += 3;
!}

= New Elections Called

**We refuse to tolerate this bourgeois government!**

The SPD will vote no confidence. New elections have been scheduled for [+ next_election_month : month +] [+ next_election_year +].

**Party Reaction:**

*"Finally, we stand with the workers!"* - Left wing

*"This is the principled position."* - Trade unions

*"We risk empowering the extremists."* - Reformist wing

**Political Situation:**
- Campaign begins immediately
- Brüning remains as caretaker
- Economic crisis deepens
- Extremists mobilizing

The election will be a referendum on democracy itself.

- @vonc_aftermath: Continue

@vonc_conditional_toleration
on-arrival: {!
Q.spd_toleration = 1;
Q.conditional_toleration = 1;
Q.time_to_election = 0;

// Slightly better than unconditional
Q.workers_spd -= 6;
Q.unemployed_spd -= 8;
Q.workers_kpd += 5;
Q.unemployed_kpd += 6;

Q.left_dissent += 12;
Q.labor_dissent += 15;
Q.centrist_dissent += 5;

Q.z_relation += 3;
Q.kpd_relation -= 8;

// Next election delayed
Q.next_election_year = Q.year + 2;
Q.next_election_month = Q.month;
Q.next_election_time = Q.time + 24;

Q.toleration_demands_made = 1;
!}

= Conditional Toleration

**We will tolerate Brüning, but with demands.**

We've extracted the following concessions:

**Brüning's Commitments:**
- Limit welfare cuts to essential minimums
- Maintain core unemployment insurance
- Consult SPD on major policy changes
- No attacks on trade union rights
- Protection of republican constitution

[? if prussian_government = "I" : - SPD retains control of Prussia ?]

**Party Reaction:**

*"Better than nothing, but still collaboration."* - Left wing

*"We've salvaged something from disaster."* - Reformist wing

*"The SPD negotiates its own irrelevance."* - KPD

This arrangement is fragile. Brüning may break his promises, and our base is still angry.

- @vonc_aftermath: Continue

@vonc_fall_braun

= Government Falls - Caretaker Administration

**The vote of no confidence has succeeded.**

However, President Braun has asked Chancellor [+ chancellor +] to remain as head of a caretaker government until new elections can be held.

**Caretaker Status:**
- No new policies can be enacted
- Government maintains basic functions
- Emergency powers only
- Elections in 3 months

New elections have been scheduled for [+ next_election_month : month +] [+ next_election_year +].

**Party Reaction:**

*"We should have made more concessions."* - Reformist wing

*"Good riddance to that failed coalition."* - Left wing

*"Now we can campaign on our real principles."* - Centrist faction

The campaign begins immediately.

- @vonc_aftermath: Continue

# ============================================
# AFTERMATH AND CONSEQUENCES
# ============================================

@vonc_aftermath
on-arrival: {!
// Track that we've been through a VONC
Q.vonc_survived = Q.vonc_resolved ? 1 : 0;
Q.vonc_failed = Q.vonc_resolved ? 0 : 1;

// Long-term consequences based on how we handled it
if (Q.vonc_survived) {
    Q.coalition_stability = "fragile";
    if (Q.spd_prussia === 0) {
        Q.organizational_strength -= 2;
    }
} else {
    Q.coalition_stability = "collapsed";
}

// Track specific outcomes for future events
if (Q.in_popular_front && Q.kpd_in_government) {
    Q.popular_front_formed_crisis = 1;
}

if (Q.spd_toleration && !Q.spd_in_government) {
    Q.toleration_start_time = Q.time;
    Q.toleration_duration = 0;
}

// Reset VONC flags for next potential crisis
Q.tried_supporting_kpd = 0;
Q.kpd_demands_seen = 0;
Q.dnvp_demands_seen = 0;
Q.vonc_delayed = 0;
!}

= Crisis Resolution

[? if vonc_survived : **The government has survived the crisis.** ?]
[? if vonc_failed : **The government has fallen.** ?]

**What we learned:**

[? if spd_prussia = 0 and vonc_survived : We sacrificed Prussia to maintain national power. This will have lasting consequences for our organizational strength. ?]

[? if welfare < 0 and vonc_survived : We enacted austerity to save the coalition. Workers are abandoning us for more radical alternatives. ?]

[? if in_popular_front and kpd_in_government : We've made history by bringing the KPD into government. This is either our salvation or our doom. ?]

[? if spd_toleration = 1 : We've entered the unprecedented position of "tolerating" a bourgeois government. How long can this last? ?]

[? if vonc_failed and time_to_election > 0 : We face new elections in a few months. The campaign will be brutal. ?]

**Internal State:**
- Left dissent: [+ left_dissent +]
- Labor dissent: [+ labor_dissent +]
- Reformist dissent: [+ reformist_dissent +]
[? if coalition_dissent > 0 : - Coalition dissent: [+ coalition_dissent +] ?]

[? if vonc_survived and coalition_dissent >= 2 : The coalition remains unstable. Another crisis could come at any time. ?]

[? if in_popular_front : The Popular Front faces opposition from both the far-right and conservative establishment. ?]

[? if spd_toleration = 1 : Every month we tolerate Brüning's austerity, we lose more workers to the KPD and NSDAP. ?]

- @root: Continue

