@toleration_crisis_1
title: Brüning Breaks His Promise
subtitle: The Chancellor enacts harsh measures despite our agreement
new-page: true
view-if: spd_toleration = 1 and conditional_toleration = 1 and time >= toleration_start_time + 3
max-visits: 1
tags: event
on-arrival: {!
Q.bruening_betrayal = 1;
Q.workers_spd -= 5;
Q.unemployed_spd -= 6;
Q.left_dissent += 10;
Q.labor_dissent += 12;
!}

= Brüning's Betrayal

**Chancellor Brüning has broken his commitments to us.**

Despite our conditional toleration agreement, Brüning has enacted:
- Massive unemployment benefit cuts
- Public sector wage reductions
- Tax increases on workers
- Attacks on union collective bargaining

He used Article 48 presidential decrees to bypass the Reichstag entirely.

**Our Options:**

- @toleration_end: End toleration and force new elections
- @toleration_protest: Protest loudly but continue toleration
- @toleration_renegotiate: Demand new negotiations

@toleration_end
on-arrival: spd_toleration = 0; time_to_election = 3; left_dissent -= 5; labor_dissent -= 8; workers_spd += 3
call: set_next_election_time

**We've ended our toleration!**

A vote of no confidence will be called. New elections in [+ next_election_month : month +] [+ next_election_year +].

*"Finally! We should never have tolerated him in the first place!"* - Left wing

@toleration_protest
on-arrival: left_dissent += 5; labor_dissent += 8; workers_spd -= 3; workers_kpd += 3

We protest Brüning's actions but continue toleration.

*"Empty words! You're still propping him up!"* - KPD

@toleration_renegotiate
choose-if: resources >= 2
unavailable-subtitle: Need 2 resources
on-arrival: resources -= 2; z_relation += 3; coalition_dissent = 0

We've extracted minor new concessions through intense negotiation.

@toleration_crisis_2
title: The Cost of Toleration
subtitle: Our base is hemorrhaging to the extremists
new-page: true
view-if: spd_toleration = 1 and time >= toleration_start_time + 6
max-visits: 1
tags: event
on-arrival: {!
Q.toleration_duration = Q.time - Q.toleration_start_time;
Q.workers_spd -= 8;
Q.unemployed_spd -= 10;
Q.workers_kpd += 6;
Q.workers_nsdap += 2;
Q.unemployed_kpd += 8;
Q.unemployed_nsdap += 2;
!}

= The Toleration Trap

**Our toleration policy is destroying us.**

After [+ toleration_duration +] months of tolerating Brüning's austerity government:

**The Numbers:**
- Workers fleeing to KPD
- Unemployed abandoning us en masse
- Trade union membership declining
- Left wing in open revolt
- Reformists demoralized

**What people are saying:**

*"The SPD tolerates our starvation!"* - Unemployed worker

*"Social fascism! The SPD enables capitalist dictatorship!"* - KPD

*"Where is the party that once fought for us?"* - Trade unionist

*"This is political suicide."* - Left SPD deputy

**Can we continue this policy?**

- @end_toleration_now: End toleration immediately
- @toleration_continue_despair: Continue despite the costs
- @toleration_extract_concessions: Demand major concessions to continue

@end_toleration_now
on-arrival: spd_toleration = 0; time_to_election = 3; left_dissent -= 10; labor_dissent -= 12; workers_spd += 5; reformist_dissent += 8
call: set_next_election_time

**Toleration policy ended!**

We will vote no confidence. Elections called for [+ next_election_month : month +] [+ next_election_year +].

*"Finally, we return to our principles!"* - Left wing

@toleration_continue_despair
on-arrival: left_dissent += 15; labor_dissent += 15; left_strength -= 5

We continue tolerating Brüning despite everything.

The party is in crisis. How much longer can this go on?

@toleration_extract_concessions
choose-if: resources >= 3 and z_relation >= 45
unavailable-subtitle: [? if resources < 3 : Need 3 resources. ?] [? if z_relation < 45 : Center Party not cooperative enough. ?]
on-arrival: resources -= 3; welfare += 1; workers_spd += 2; left_dissent -= 5

We've forced Brüning to restore some welfare spending.

A minor victory, but is it enough?

