@left_front_vonc
title: KPD Threatens to Leave Coalition
subtitle: The Communists are unhappy with our reformist policies
new-page: true
view-if: (in_left_front or in_popular_front) and kpd_coalition_dissent >= 4 and kpd_in_government
max-visits: 1
tags: event
on-arrival: {!
Q.kpd_crisis = 1;
!}

= Communist Crisis

**The KPD is threatening to leave the coalition!**

[? if kpd_party_leader = "Conciliators" : Even the Conciliator leadership is under pressure from the party base. ?]
[? if kpd_party_leader != "Conciliators" : The hardline KPD leadership demands immediate revolutionary action. ?]

**Their Grievances:**

[? if welfare < 1 : "You've cut welfare instead of expropriating the capitalists!" ?]
[? if nationalization < 2 : "Where is the socialization of industry we were promised?" ?]
[? if reichswehr_minister_party != "KPD" : "The military remains in reactionary hands!" ?]
[? if kpd_coalition_dissent >= 5 : "The SPD has betrayed the working class once again!" ?]

**KPD Demands:**
- Immediate nationalization of key industries
- Worker control in factories
- Disarm right-wing paramilitary groups
- Purge reactionaries from civil service
- Aggressive anti-fascist policies

**What should we do?**

- @left_front_accommodate: Accommodate KPD demands
- @left_front_negotiate: Negotiate a compromise
- @left_front_refuse: Refuse their ultimatum
- @left_front_let_them_go: Let the KPD leave

@left_front_accommodate
on-arrival: {!
Q.kpd_coalition_dissent = 0;
Q.kpd_relation += 10;
Q.nationalization += 1;
Q.workers_spd += 5;
Q.workers_kpd -= 3;
Q.left_dissent -= 10;
Q.reformist_dissent += 20;
Q.coup_progress += 2;
Q.capital_strike_progress += 3;
!}

= Radical Turn

**We've accepted the KPD's demands.**

Major nationalization begins. Worker councils gain power. Anti-fascist crackdowns intensify.

**Consequences:**
- KPD satisfied for now
- Left wing energized
- Reformists horrified
- Coup risk increased dramatically
- Capital flight accelerating

*"Finally, real socialism!"* - Left SPD

*"This is madness! We're provoking civil war!"* - Reformists

The right-wing is mobilizing for confrontation.

@left_front_negotiate
choose-if: resources >= 3
unavailable-subtitle: Need 3 resources
on-arrival: resources -= 3; kpd_coalition_dissent -= 2; kpd_relation += 3; reformist_dissent += 8

We've negotiated a middle path with partial concessions.

The crisis is defused, but tensions remain.

@left_front_refuse
on-arrival: kpd_coalition_dissent += 2; kpd_relation -= 10; left_dissent += 10

We've refused the KPD's ultimatum.

They may leave the coalition soon.

@left_front_let_them_go
on-arrival: {!
Q.kpd_in_government = 0;
Q.in_left_front = 0;
Q.in_popular_front = 0;
Q.kpd_relation -= 15;
Q.workers_kpd += 8;
Q.workers_spd -= 6;
Q.coalition_votes = Q.coalition_votes - Q.kpd_r;

// Check if government still viable
Q.coalition_viable = Q.coalition_votes >= 50;

if (!Q.coalition_viable) {
    Q.time_to_election = 3;
}
!}
go-to: left_front_collapse_viable if coalition_viable; left_front_collapse_new_elections if not coalition_viable

@left_front_collapse_viable

The KPD has left the coalition.

[? if in_popular_front : The Popular Front has collapsed. ?]
[? if in_left_front : The Left Front has collapsed. ?]

However, our remaining coalition partners still command a Reichstag majority.

We must find new partners or govern as a weakened coalition.

@left_front_collapse_new_elections
call: set_next_election_time

The KPD has left the coalition, and we no longer have a Reichstag majority.

New elections have been called for [+ next_election_month : month +] [+ next_election_year +].

*"The united front was a disaster!"* - Reformists

*"The KPD betrayed workers' unity!"* - Left SPD

